    <h1 style="flex: 1;">Congrats on deploying to Aptible!</h1>

    <h3 style="color: #4361FF;">You're seeing this page because you've hit a 500 error.</h3>

    <p>
      If this is your first time deploying, it's probably because
      you don't have a Database associated with your App.
    </p>

    <p>
      If it's not and you want to stop seeing our custom 500 error page, edit the
      <code>config/routes.rb</code> file.
    </p>

    <p>
      This template is supposed to be used with a PostgreSQL Database,
      which you can provision on Aptible through the CLI using
      <code>aptible db:create</code>
      or through the Dashboard by pressing Create Database.
    </p>

    <p>
      Once you have your database created, set the configuration variable
      <code>DATABASE_URL</code>
      to the database's connection string and redeploy!
    </p>
